cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TC, cs.DS, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category as the paper deals with a formal system (lambda calculus) and proposes a cost model for it. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper deals with the call-by-value lambda calculus, which is a programming language. 
- cs.TC (Theoretical Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper proposes a cost model that satisfies the invariance thesis, which is a theoretical concept. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper proposes a cost model that takes into account the size of intermediate results, which is related to data structures. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper proposes a cost model that aims to simulate Turing machines within a polynomial time overhead, which is related to computational complexity.
